time complexity: O(a+b)
space complexity: O(a+b)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: This solution uses a greedy approach to construct the string. It iterates through the string, always preferring to add "aab" if possible, then "a", then "b". This ensures that the substrings "aaa" and "bbb" are avoided. The time complexity is O(a+b) because each character is added at most once, and the space complexity is O(a+b) because the resulting string has length a+b.

